If Statement: 
-> This is a decision making statement, which will execute it's code if and only if the condition is true.
-> e.g. if(condition)
        {
        Statements; // Codes
        }
        
If-Else Statement: 
-> In this the 'else' codes will execute if and only if the condition is false.
-> e.g. if(condition)
        {
        Statement; // odes
        }
        else
        {
        Statement; // Codes
        }

If-Else-If:
-> This is combination of if-else statement.
-> e.g. if(condition)
		{
        Statements;
        }
        else if(Condition)
        {
        Statements
        }
        else if(Condition)
        {
        Statement;
        }
        else
        {
        Statement;
        }